fields.value: Religious Attitude, Self-Consciousness, Self Monitoring Scales (CAPS-SELFCM and CAPS-PPSELFCM and CAPS-FSELFCM module)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit consists of three parts: (1) a 6-item religious attitude measure, (2) Fenigstein Self-consciousness scale, (3) Snyder Self Monitoring Scale.

SELFCM consists of the responses of CAPS respondents. In CAPS86 the unit was also administered in a paper and pencil version (PPSELFCM) and to the respondents' same-sex friend (in FSELFCM).

RELIGIOUS ATTITUDES Five items, taken from Thurstone and Chave's (1929) Attitudes toward the Church Scale, were used to assess attitudes toward religion. An additional item used by Zanna it al (1980) was included.

FENIGSTEIN SELF-CONSCIOUSNESS SCALE The 23 item Self-consciousness Scale is a measure of the consistent tendency of persons to direct attention inward or outward. Development of the scale indicates two major components of self-consciousness -- public and private. The private self-consciousness concerns the process of attending to one's inner thoughts and feelings while public self-consciousness is a general awareness of self as a social object that has an effect on others. A third compone nt is social anxiety, or discomfort in the presence of others. The public and private self-consciousness is the process of self-focused attention while social anxiety is a reaction to this process.

See codebook for additional information

SNYDER SELF-MONITORING SCALE This 25-item scale purports to measure individual differences in concern about the appropriateness of social behavior and attention to or use of situational cues for monitoring self-presentation. It has a one month test-retest reliability of +.84 (Snyder, 1974). Factor analyses of the scale suggest that it contains three orthogonal factors (Briggs et al, 1980, Gabrenya and Arkin, 1980, Penner and Wymenr, 1983): Act ing, Extraversion, and Other Directedness.

NOTE: This administration of the Snyder Self-Monitoring scale uses a 5-point scale format. Another version (SELFMON) was administered in CAPS/85, CAPS/86, CAPS/87 and CAPS/88 using a T/F answer format.
